House Resolution 951
By: Representatives Kelley of the 16th and Smith of the 18th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing April 2025 as Child Abuse Prevention Month; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, children are vital to our state's future success, prosperity, and quality of life, as
3 well as being our most vulnerable assets; and
4 WHEREAS, all children deserve to have the safe, stable, and nurturing homes and
5 communities they need to foster their healthy growth and development; and
6 WHEREAS, child abuse and neglect is a community responsibility affecting both the current
7 and future quality of life of a community; and
8 WHEREAS, communities that provide parents with social support, knowledge of parenting
9 and child development, and concrete resources needed to cope with stress and nurture their
10 children ensure that all children grow to their full potential; and
11 WHEREAS, effective child abuse prevention strategies succeed because of partnerships
12 created among citizens, human service agencies, schools, faith communities, health care
13 providers, civic organizations, law enforcement agencies, and the business community.
